onl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me compare the current session state against the heartbeat state.\n\nCurrent time: 11:05 UTC.\n\n**Current active sessions:**\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — THIS session (running) — started ~11:05 UTC\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — running — started 1776152701090 = 08:05 UTC — running for ~3h\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ac986a8d-2425-40c7-835b-ed9b101b0bff` — running — started 1776156271891 = 10:24 UTC — running for ~41min\n\n\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — running — started 1776152701090 = 08:05 UTC — running for ~3h\n\nLooking at the heartbeat state from 11:01 UTC, the 5p cron was already running with the same status, the QLHV Ecosystem Group had ended at 10:43 UTC, and the DTLX 5p cron was marked as ended.\n\nThe DTLX Ecosystem Group, Lead Direct Session, and main session were all ended by 10:55 UTC or earlier. Comparing this to the current state at 11:05 UTC, I'm seeing that both cron sessions (e7885813 and ed2d0b5d) are still running, though the Telegram retry cron appears to be stuck and retrying. The 5p cron has been active for nearly 3 hours, the Telegram retry cron for about 41 minutes, and the DTLX 5p cron is also still running.\n\nNothing has actually changed in terms of session state since the last heartbeat at 11:01 UTC—everything's been stable. The previous report at 10:59 UTC already flagged the Telegram retry cron as stuck, and that's still the situation now. Since there's nothing new to report, I should just update the heartbeat state file and exit silently."},{"type":"text","text":"No changes from last heartbeat (11:01 UTC). Only this cron session is new. Silent — updating state only.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zspl85cjtc2z_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-revi